# gpsim command script: drive the PIC10F320 footswitch and snapshot PORTA/LATA.
#
# WHAT THIS IS
#   A register-level functional check of the PIC shell (bypass_mcu_pic10f320.c)
#   running inside gpsim. The pure debounce core and the output drivers are
#   already covered by the host/formal suite and (on AVR) by simavr lock-step;
#   the PIC SHELL -- oscillator/TMR2 tick, footswitch read on RA3, the debounce
#   integrate/step wiring, and the GPIO outputs -- has no simavr equivalent, so
#   this drives the real built HEX in gpsim and asserts the observable register
#   state at four settled checkpoints. The wrapper test/pic/run_gpsim_test.sh
#   parses the snapshots and turns them into PASS/FAIL.
#
# HOW IT IS RUN (see the wrapper / `make pic-test-gpsim`)
#   gpsim -i -pp10f320 <variant>.hex -c test/pic/footswitch_toggle.stc
#   The HEX (any of the three variants) is supplied on the gpsim command line, so
#   this script is variant-agnostic. gpsim names the PIC pins ra0..ra3.
#
# PINS (per bypass_mcu_pic10f320.c)
#   RA3 = footswitch (input; high = released, low = pressed)
#   RA0 = status LED  (LATA bit 0; high = effect ENGAGED, low = BYPASS)
#   RA1/RA2 = the active variant's control output(s)
#
# TIMING
#   FOSC = 16 MHz -> instruction clock FOSC/4 = 4 MHz -> 4000 cycles per 1 ms.
#   The debounce needs PRESSED_THRESH(8) low samples to register a press and
#   RELEASE_THRESH(25) high samples to re-arm; the relay/mute drivers also block
#   ~12 ms per actuation. All checkpoints below are placed well clear of those
#   windows so every variant has SETTLED by the time it is sampled.
#
# SCENARIO (two MOMENTARY presses; the effect latches between them)
#   cyc      0..100k  : released  -> BYPASS (power-on default)
#   cyc 100k..220k    : press #1  (~30 ms)  -> toggles to ENGAGED, then released
#   cyc 220k..520k    : released, effect stays ENGAGED (latching)
#   cyc 520k..640k    : press #2  (~30 ms)  -> toggles back to BYPASS
#
# CHECKPOINTS (the wrapper keys on these exact === labels ===)
#   INIT_BYPASS  @  90k : LATA bit0 == 0 (LED off), PORTA bit3 == 1 (released)
#   PRESS1_LOW   @ 150k : PORTA bit3 == 0 (pressed), LATA bit0 == 1 (LED latched
#                         ENGAGED -- the effect toggled ON the press, not release)
#   ENGAGED      @ 300k : LATA bit0 == 1 (LED on, latched), PORTA bit3 == 1
#   BYPASS_AGAIN @ 800k : LATA bit0 == 0 (toggled back off)

stimulus asynchronous_stimulus
  initial_state 1
  { 100000, 0,
    220000, 1,
    520000, 0,
    640000, 1 }
  name fsw
end

node n1
attach n1 fsw ra3

break c 90000
run
echo ===INIT_BYPASS===
porta
lata

break c 150000
run
echo ===PRESS1_LOW===
porta
lata

break c 300000
run
echo ===ENGAGED===
porta
lata

break c 800000
run
echo ===BYPASS_AGAIN===
porta
lata

quit
